Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Cook pasta according to directions. Closer to the end of the pasta cooking, heat oil in pan and add garlic. Saut for about 1 minute. Reduce heat to medium-low. Do not brown garlic. Combine sun dried tomatoes, basil, pepper flakes, salt and cheese for about 1 to 2 minutes. Pour oil mixture over pasta and mix. Serve with additional shredded asiago cheese on top. For additional flavour you can add kalamata olives to the pan and saut with sun dried tomatoe mixture.

Heat 2 t olive oil in a skillet that you can eventually place under the broiler. Add onion to skillet and cook until soft, about 4 minutes. Add 1 t olive oil and heat. Add eggs seasoned with salt, pepper, parsley and cheese. Cook until bottom of frittata begins to solidify. Gently place the rounds of tomato on the egg mixture. Cover and cook over low heat until bottom of frittata begins to solidify. Cover and cook over low heat until bottom of frittata firms, about 5 minutes. Finish by placing under preheated broiler for a minute or two until lightly browned. Cut into triangles.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a medium bowl mix butter, orange liqueur, orange rind, pecan halves, salt. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in pecans. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees f. For 11-14 minutes or until light golden. Transfer cookies to wire rack to cool.

In a nonreactive bowl, combine mustard, garlic, vinegar, salt and pepper with 2 teaspoons water. Slowly whisk in olive oil, forming a creamy marinade. Stir in basil. Add the chops to the marinade and coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour and up to four hours. Remove from refrigerator and let sit until arriving at room temperature. Heat grill to very hot. Remove excess marinade from chops and grill uncovered about 3 minutes per side for medium rare. Transfer to a warm platter and serve. Preparation time does not include marinade and sitting time.

Heat oven to 400 degrees f. In a food processor, combine the cheese and butter. Process until the mixture is smooth. Add the scallions and pulse until combined. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Spread the cheese mixture on the cut sides of the bread. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden. Remove from oven and serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish with nonstick pan coating or grease lightly with solid shortening. Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes. Place half in a prepared baking dish. Sprinkle half of the salt, pepper and bacon. Top with half of the sour cream & cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with chopped green onions to garnish.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut chicken in half. Arrange, skin side up, in a roasting pan. Combine butter, lemon juice, and spices in a small bowl and mix well. Brush chicken with mixture. Roast until juices run clear. Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a large bowl, combine the egg, breadcrumbs, parmesan cheese, milk and onion. Remove sausage from casings. Add sausage to the bread crumb mixture and mix well. Shape into 20 meatballs. Arrange meatballs on a shallow baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes or until meatballs are cooked through. Serve with your favorite sauce and spaghetti.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. Place pork loin roast in crock pot and place in crock pot on low for 5-6 hours. Add paprika, cayenne, garlic powder, oregano, salt, black pepper, potatoes, baby carrots, chicken broth. Cover and cook on low power for 5-6 hours. Remove pork loin roast to a plate and temporarily set aside. In fat in skillet, saute sliced onion and minced garlic, seasoned with the poultry seasoning, just until onion starts to soften. Place in bottom of slow cooker. Turn heat to high and add white wine to skillet. Scrape up all the bits sticking to skillet, then pour this mixture over the onions in the crock pot. Cover onions with cubed raw sweet potato. Place browned pork loin roast on top of sweet potato cubes, then pour chicken stock over roast. Cover and cook on low power for for 7 to 8 hours, or until sweet potatoes are tender and pork is cooked.

Heat oil in a large saute or fry pan until very hot. Add vegetables all at once, spreading in an even layer. Do not stir until bottom of layer begins to brown. Flip and stir to get unbrowned pieces to bottom. Let cook until beginning to brown. The trick here is to keep heat high and brown pieces without overcooking or burning them. If pieces are browned, but not soft enough for your taste, turn off heat and cover pan for a few minutes.

Boil water in a large saucepan over high heat. When water comes to a rapid boil, turn off heat, put the tea bags into water and cover. After the tea has steeped about 1 hour, pour the sugar into a 2-quart pitcher, then add tea. The tea should still be warm so the sugar will dissolve easily. Add lemon juice. Chill. Makes 2 quarts.

Preheat oven to 450f. Grease 9x 13 pan. Beat everything together. Pour into pan. Bake 30-35 minutes until center tests clean with knife or toothpick. Remove from oven and let cool completely before cutting into squares. Important to cool completely so it sets up firmly before cutting.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees f. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add peanuts and stir to combine. Transfer peanuts to baking sheet. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chili powder and toss. Cool and then transfer to airtight containers. Store at least 8 hours before serving.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir in the onion, garlic, and bay leaf, and saute until onion is lightly browned. Preheat oven to 180 degrees celsius. Place chopped butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl and beat until light and creamy. Add egg and vanilla. Mix through flours and coconut until a soft dough forms. Mix chocolate chips into the dough. Using your hands, mould two tablespoons of dough mixture into a flat round. Place rounds on a baking tray that is lined with non stick baking paper. Repeat until all the mixture is used. Bake for 10 minutes or until light golden. Allow to cool on trays.
Heat oven to 400. Place the peppers in a large roasting pan and cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 15 to 30 minutes, or until the peppers are cooked through. Serve hot.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Spray a large baking pan with cooking spray. Rub the fillets on both sides with lemon juice, then salt and pepper them to taste. Place fillets in the baking disk and sprinkle evenly with tarragon. Cover evenly with sour cream. Bake for about 15 minutes until fish is done but not over cooked. Sprinkle with chives and parsley.

Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Stir in hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste. Add in crabmeat and shrimp. Cook and stir over low heat until shrimp turn pink. Add in parsley and stir to combine. Serve.

In a blender, blend water and sugar until the sugar dissolves. Add orange blossom water, blood orange juice and lemon juice. Stir. Pour through a strainer into ice-filled glasses. You should end up with about 1 cup of liquid. Stir in lime juice and agave. Garnish with lime and mint, and serve.
Mix ingredients in a large non-reactive bowl or one gallon food storage bag. Add the margarita s to a blender and liquify. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Put the mint leaves in a large baking dish. Arrange the potatoes and the red and green peppers alternately in a spoke pattern in a shallow, 12-inch round baking dish. Pile the mint leaves in the center. Scatter the garlic over the top. Drizzle with oil, and sprinkle with rosemary, salt and black pepper. Bake in the preheated oven until the vegetables are lightly golden and tender, or about 45 minutes. Garnish with fresh mint sprigs.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350f. Mix wet ingredients with dry ingredients, and lastly stir in the oats and chocolate chips. Form into small balls with hands and bake on cookie sheets lined with parchment paper for 8-10 minutes or until very light golden, they should almost look un-cooked. Store in a tupperware box to keep them chewy.

Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix thoroughly. Form into 4 -6 patties. Grill on med. For 5 - 7 minutes on each side. Top with mozzarella cheese slices. Sliced black olives and extra pizza sauce.

Heat oil in skillet, add onion, pepper, tomatoes, cilantro, garlic and tomato paste. Cook for 10 minutes. Bring to a boil, then add shrimp and lemon juice. Reduce heat to medium and cook for 2 minutes. Add coconut milk and stir-fry 3-4 minutes until shrimp are pink and opaque. Add cilantro. Toss well and transfer to serving plates. Top each serving with 1 tablespoon toasted coconut and 1 tablespoon chopped peanuts. Garnish with lime wedges.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees fahrenheit. Grease a 13x9x2 inch pan. Unroll dough. Press in bottom and 1 inch up sides of greased pan. Place pieces of butter along the inside edges of dough. Fold the 1 inch of dough over and around the cheese. Bake at 425 degrees fahrenheit for 15 to 18 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees and spray a 10 x 15 inch pan with cooking spray. Place the cauliflower in a large bowl, drizzle with oil and toss to coat. Spread the cauliflower in prepared pan and sprinkle with any remaining crumbs. Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.

Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and saut, stirring frequently, until softened and translucent, about 3 minutes. Add the ground beef to the skillet, breaking it up well with a spoon, and cook until the meat has lost its raw color, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently to break up any clumps. Add 2 cups ketchup, the chili powder, garlic powder, pepper flakes, salt and stir well to mix. Cook, uncovered, until the meat is cooked through and the flavors are blended, about 20 minutes, stirring frequently to break up any clumps. Add 2 cups ketchup, the chili powder,

In a large pot, combine chicken stock, eggs, parmesan cheese, fresh italian parsley, salt & freshly ground black pepper. Stir occasionally over medium heat until chicken is hot, 1 to 2 minutes. Add chicken. Cover and simmer for 10-12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add in the sausage and spinach. Cook until well heated.

In a small saucepan, heat butter and oil over medium-high heat. Saute onion until softened, about 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, stir to incorporate, and bring to boiling point. Cover pan, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork, season with salt if needed, and serve hot.

Heat oven to 400 degrees fahrenheit. On a cutting board, with a fork, mass the salmon into a paste with the salt and pepper. Add the butter and mash into garlic paste. Arrange the salmon in a single layer in a baking dish. Top it with the garlic butter and drizzle with lemon wedges. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until salmon is just cooked through. Sprinkle with the parsley and serve with lemon wedges.

In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine cup water, sugar and lemon zest. Bring to a boil, then decrease heat and simmer for 3 minutes. Set aside to cool. Strain syrup through sieve placed over large measuring cup, discarding solids. Whisk in lemon juice and remaining 2 cups water. Pour into molds and freeze until slushy, then insert sticks and freeze until solid, for at least 4 hours. If you are using an ice pop kit, follow the manufacturers instructions.

In a large skillet, heat oil to medium-high heat. Add chicken and brown. Put chicken in crockpot. Add frozen vegetables and tapioca. Mix well. In a small bowl, mix all remaining ingredients. Pour on the chicken. Cover and bake at low heat for 4 hours.

Place beans in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until crisp-tender. Meanwhile, in a skillet, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in water chestnuts and seasonings. Heat through. Drain beans and stir into skillet. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

Preheat over to 375f. Dredge filets in butter. Dredge filets in bread crumbs. Dredge filets in minced garlic. Sprinkle with seasoning salt. Spay small casserole dish add filets and bake covered with foil for 25 minutes. Uncover and broil for 3 or more minutes, depending on if ya want them crispier. Good served with rice and veggie of your choice.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until just moistened. Spoon into lined or nonstick, sprayed muffin pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove muffins from the tray and cool on a wire rack.

In a small saucepan over medium low heat, melt 3 tbls butter. Stir flour and salt into pan until creamed together. Slowly stir in cream, then stir in cream cheese, increase heat to medium. Constantly whisk until mixture becomes thick and smooth, remove from heat and set aside. In a small saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onions and garlic in remaining butter until translucent. Add spinach and water to pan, reduce heat to low, cover. Cook, stirring occasionally for 8 minutes. Stir prepared sauce and parmesan cheese into pan, stir until completely blended.

In a small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Stir in sugar, vanilla, salt, and milk. Bring to a boil over medium-low heat. Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake. The amount of time will vary with the amount of sauce being reheated.
In a large skillet, combine the bacon, zucchini, cherry tomatoes, olive oil, pesto sauce, parmesan cheese, and toss to combine. Pour over chicken or warm bread.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees fahrenheit. Unroll squares into 4 rectangles and place in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Press up sides slightly and press perforations together. Layer cooked sausage, bacon, onion, green pepper, red pepper, cheddar and colby cheese. At this point you can make it ahead and refrigerate for up to 24 hours. Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over the dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

Wtih processor running, drop garlic through feed tube and mince. Scrape down sides of work bowl. Add chickpeas, tahini and lemon juice. Process until mixture is smooth. Add roasted peppers. Process until peppers are finely chopped. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer hummus to small bowl.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Brush a large baking dish with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil. Put green beans, onion, and garlic in dish, drizzle with remaining oil and sprinkle with salt. Bake for 25 minutes, stirring beans at least 3 times. When tender, remove beans from oven and transfer to bowl. Immediately drizzle with vinegar. Add shallots to the skillet drippings. Cook over medium-high heat until golden brown, about 6 minutes. Add balsamic vinegar and cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Place green beans in large pot of lightly salted, boiling water. Cook until just crisp-tender, 5-6 minutes. Drain immediately and add green beans to shallot mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Toss until coated, place in dish, sprinkle pancetta over top, and serve.

Place potatoes in water and 1 tsp salt and simmer until tender, about 15 to 18 minutes. Drain and run under cold water to cool. Cut into quarters. Meanwhile, cook bacon in skillet untel crisp. Crumble when cooled. Whisk oil, vinegar, mustard, remaining salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Toss with the potatoes, bacon and parsley.

Preheat oven to 325f. In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips and margarine over low heat, stirring until foamy and light yellow in color. Beat in sugar, vanilla, and chip mixture. Add flour, mixing well. Pour into a lightly greased 13x9-inch pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan or until set in center. Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and zucchini mixture. Cover and cook for 15 minutes over low heat. Add chicken and z

Heat oil in a saute pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and stir for around 5 minutes until golden, but not burned or bitter. Remove pan from heat, let cool. Place 1 sandwich into skillet. Cook, turning once, until sandwich is golden brown, about 4-5 minutes. Repeat with remaining sandwiches. Cook,

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Spread almonds onto a baking sheet in a single layer. Roast about 10 to 15 minutes, until slightly browned, tossing a couple of times for even browning. Let cool to touch. In a blender, mix or pulse the almonds with the walnut oil and salt. This can take about 10 minutes or so. Once smooth, spoon in honey and blend for 30 seconds to mix thoroughly. Spread on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 30 minutes, until slightly browned, tossing a couple of times for even browning. Spread on an un

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and egg whites. Beat in milk, honey and vanilla. Stir in bread cubes. Pour into 8 inch baking dish, sprayed with a non-stick spray. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. Serve hot.

In a large pot with boiling salted water cook pasta until al dente. Drain. In a large saucepan heat the italian dressing and olive oil together over medium heat. Add drained spaghetti. Toss well to coat. Add chopped tomatoes, cooked chicken, and grated parmesan cheese and toss lightly. Serve warm.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees f or grill to medium-high. Sprinkle both sides of steak with garlic powder and pepper. Cut in thin strips. Combine steak strips and pepper strips with teriyaki sauce. Center one-fourth of the steak mixture on each sheet of foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets. Bake 12 to 15 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or grill 7 to 9 minutes in covered grill. Serve immediately over rice. Makes 4 servings.

Bring rice and water to a boil in a 3 quart heavy saucepan, then reduce, heat to low and cook, tightly covered, until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Gently stir rice from top to bottom of saucepan with a heatproof rubber spatula. Cook bacon in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until golden and crisp, about 6 minutes. Pour into a sieve set over a heatproof bowl and reserve bacon and fat separately. Whisk together eggs, t salt and t pepper in a medium bowl. Return 3 tablespoons fat to skillet and saut onion over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until eggs are just set, about 1 minute. Add rice, remaining teaspoon salt and remaining teaspoon pepper and cook, stirring, 2 minutes. Add rice, remaining teaspoon salt and remaining teaspoon

In a large, heavy bottomed, skillet place the sugar and water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add the almonds and cook, stirring constantly, until almost all the water has evaporated. About 5 minutes. Add the cinnamon and salt and cook until the sugar has dried on the almonds. About 2 minutes. Pour onto a large sheet pan and let cool.

Preheat oven to 425. Spread the vegetables in a single layer in one or more large shallow roasting pans. Do not crowd them or they will not brown. Drizzle with the oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Stir well. Roast the vegetables, stirring once or twice, for 45 minutes. Place the sausages on top of the vegetables. Bake for 15 to 30 minutes, or until the sausages and vegetables are cooked through. Serve hot.

Heat oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Add ziti pasta, butter, cream cheese, garlic powder, milk, parmesan cheese, ground black pepper, parsley flakes. Stir until creamy and thick. Turn off the heat and stir in nutritional yeast. Serve over your choice of pasta.

Heat 2 teaspoons of oil over high heat and add 4 rashers of butter and cook for 2-3 minutes or until crip and then set aside. Heat another 2 teaspoons of oil in the pan and add chopped brown onion and garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add potatoes, 2 sprigs thyme, chicken stock and water and bring to the boil and then reduce heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes. Blend until smooth and stir through cream. Divide into serving bowls and top with crispy bacon to serve.

Preheat oven to 350f. Place chips on a foil-lined baking sheet. Top with salsa, beans, scallions and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted. Top with guacamole. Enjoy with vegetable sticks dipped in dressing.

Place all ingredients in a roaster. Cover the roaster with plastic wrap and then foil to seal. Bake at 250 for 8 hours. Remove coverings and stir. Remove bone and cartilage as meat will have fallen off. Turn oven up to 350. Continue cooking for 1 hour stirring occasionally as the dish caramelizes. Serve with mashed potatoes.

In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter or margarine. Add garlic and onion and cook until onion is re-hydtrated. Add tomatoes, green chili, salt and cilantro. Add water. Simmer for 30 minutes. This can also be made in a crock pot. Add okra, turnip greens, okra, onion, pine nuts, jalapeno peppers, water, salt and cilantro

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. In a bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and butter with your hands. Press the mixture firmly into a 9-inch pie pan, and bake until brown, about 20 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow to cool to room temperature before filling. Lower the oven temperature to 325 degrees f. In a separate bowl, combine the condensed milk, lime juice, and eggs. Whisk until well blended and place the filling in the cooled pie shell. Bake in the oven for 15 minutes and allow to chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Once chilled, combine the sour cream and powdered sugar and spread over the top of the pie using a spatula. Sprinkle the lime zest as a garnish on top of the sour cream and serve chilled.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 8x8 square pan. Melt butter and cool slightly and add milk and beaten egg, set to the side. In bowl, sift the next four ingredients, 2 times. Add butter, milk, and egg mixture and stir only enough to smooth out any lumps. Combine the remaining sugar and cinnamon for the topping, in a small bowl or in a ziploc bag. Pour batter into greased pan and sprinkle the mixture of sugar and cinnamon over the top and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisins, ground nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk,

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Coat a 2 quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cook the macaroni according to package directions. Drain and place in a large bowl. Add the remaining ingredents except for the corn chips. Mix well then pour into a casserol dish and sprinkle with corn chips bake for 30-35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly, and the top is golden.

Heat oil in a skillet over high heat. Brown chicken in two batches, 6 to 8 minutes. Set aside. In same skillet over medium heat, cook ginger, onion, and garlic, stirring until browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Add soy sauce, vinegar, and sugar. Cook over high heat until thick, 3 to 4 minutes. Add chicken. Stir to warm. Remove from heat. Stir in scallions.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In an ovenproof saucepan or dutch oven, heat oil on medium-high heat. Add pork sausage, ground beef, cayenne pepper, black pepper, salt, onion, celery, green bell pepper, long grain rice and cook, stirring, 4 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Butter the sides and bottom of a 10-inch springform pan and set aside. In the top of a double boiler, combine the butter, chocolate and coffee and melt slowly, stirring occasionally, until smooth. Remove from the heat and let cool for 5 minutes. In a medium mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, sugar and vanilla until frothy. Whisk the eggs into the melted chocolate until combined. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour and cool on a wire rack until it reaches room temperature. Remove the sides of the pan, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight, before serving.
Put sweet and hot pickles in a large, nonreactive pot. Bring to a boil. When it starts boiling, pack into jars. Wipe rims, and cap, using sterilized lids and bands. Let set for 6 weeks before eating.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a plastic bag, combine cheese, flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Place potatoes inthe bag and toss to coat with mixture. Pour butter into an 8x8-inch baking dish. Stir in potatoes, coating well. Bake at 350 degrees f for 1 hour and 15 minutes, to 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Preheat oven to 400f degrees. Mix all ingredients in lg bowl. Mix well. Pour into crust. Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 and bake another 40 min, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Garnish with pecans if desired.

In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until no longer pink. Stir in the soup, water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stin in sour cream. Serve over toasted english muffins. Can also serve over cooked noodles. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper or paprika.

Spray a nonstick frypan with veggies cooking spray and heat to medium. Spray veggie cooking spray over both sides of the cod fillets. Sprinkle parsley, italian seasoning, salt and pepper over both sides of the cod fillets. Place cod into medium hot frypan, cook for about 5 minutes, carefully turn and cook a further 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve hot with the other 2 lemon sections for garnish.

In a large shallow baking pan, toast eggs in 325 oven, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar and salt, beating until stiff. Fold in toasted egg yolks. Melt butter in same pan. Spread nut mixture on top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325 or until nut are browned and butter is absorbed. Stir nuts thoroughly every 10 minutes during baking.

Heat oil in cast iron skillet until it reaches 350 or flour bubbles immediately upon being sprinkled in it. Place the soy sauce, vinegar and oil in a screw-top jar and shake until well combined. Place the oysters on a large serving platter. Drizzle over the soy and sesame dressing. Sprinkle with the green shallots. Serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 400f. Peel and cube squash. In a large bowl mix minced garlic and olive oil. Add cubed squash and coat with the oil mixture. Dump all ingredients out of bowl and in to a glass casserole dish. Any size will do really but it will cook faster if it is more spread out. Cook 40-45 minutes, stirring once or twice. Squash is done when it is tender.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until they look fairly cooked and shiny. Add almonds and saut for a couple more minutes. Finally, add frozen green beans and splash of soy sauce. Stir frequently until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

Preheat oven to 350f. In a large mixing bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat together butter and shortening until light and fluffy. Add sugar and cream together until very light. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg. Gradually fold in flour until a soft, workable dough forms. Shape into balls and place on cookie sheets. Dip the bottom of a flat bottomed glass in sugar and use it to mash down the balls of dough. Bake in preheated oven until done. Immediately remove from pan to cool.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Coat a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except the bacon and mix well. Pour into the baking dish and lay the raw strips of bacon on top. Cover and bake for approximately 45 minutes, or until thick and bubbly. Uncover and bake for 5 more minute.

In a large skillet, melt butter over medium-low heat. Add bacon, red potatoes, onion, green pepper, eggs, milk, salt, pepper, cheddar cheese. Cook and stir until eggs are completely set. Sprinkle with cheese and let stand until cheese has melted.

Preheat oven to 400degf. Combine all ingredients on a large greased baking sheet. Arrange in a single layer. Roast in preheated oven for about 50 minutes, turning once during cooking, until potatoes are tender. Bake in the preheated oven until potatoes are tender, or about 45 minutes. Garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large saucepan over medium high heat, add the shrimp. Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, for about 4 minutes or until onions turn pink and are thoroughly cooked. Add the shrimp, onion and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, for about 4 minutes or until onions turn pink and are thoroughly cooked

Heat the oil in a wok over a medium heat for 1 minute. Add the chicken and stir-fry for 5 minutes or until golden. Stir in the vegetables and stir-fry for 5 minutes, or until tender-crisp. Transfer the contents of the wok to a large salad bowl, add the salad greens and mix well. Whisk together the dressing and the soy sauce in a small bowl, drizzle it over the salad-vegetable mixture and mix well. Whisk together the dressing and the soy sauce in a small bowl, drizzle it over the salad-vegetable mixture

Preheat oven to 200c or 180c fan forced. Place salmon in a baking dish and pour over stock and season, cover with foil and bake for 10 to 15 minutes o until just cooked through. Remove from oven and cool salmon in stock for 10 minutes. Remove the salmon from the stock. Add sour cream, cucumber, wine and tarragon to stock and whisk to combine, season and transfer to a jug. Meanwhile steam potato over a saucepan of simmering water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Place salmon and potato on plates and top salmon with cucumber sauce and tarragon leaves and drizzle oil over potatoes and season and serve.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all 3 ingredients. In a small mixing bowl, combine all 3 ingredients. In a small mixing bowl, combine all 3

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl. The dough should form a ball -- not too dry, but not too sticky either. If you have mixed for a long time, and there is still a lot of flour in the bowl, add a tiny bit more water. If the dough is too wet, add more flour. Cover the ball of dough with a thin dusting of flour, so you can remove it from the bowl. Using floured hands, spread the dough onto a greased cookie sheet -- the dough should be thin enough cover the entire sheet. Bake for 25 minutes at 350. Transfer to a cooling rack to cool, and cut into 12 slices.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a small micorwave safe bowl combine butter, honey and lemon juice. Microwave until butter melts, add cinnamon. Place cubed potatoes in a large bowl and pour honey mixture over potatoes, toss to coat. Place in a roasting pan, salt and bake for about 50 minutes, or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Heat oil in a saut pan over medium heat, add the garlic and cook until golden. Add the anchovies and saut until the outsides are just browned. Stir through the basil leaves and pine nuts and serve.

Preheat oven to 400f. To make pimento cheese, blend the cheese with the butter. Stir in the flour, salt, paprika, pimento stuffed olives. Mix well. Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive overlapping completely. Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

Mix all ingredients together and place them in a casserole dish. Cover with crushed potato chips and sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered at 350f. For about 30 minutes or until heated through and chips are lighty brown. Serve with noodles and a salad.
Heat oil in wok and shallow fry a few at a time until golden brown. Drain on paper towel and serve.

Heat oil in large skillet over high heat. Add onion and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add garlic and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add salt and pepper and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add lemon juice and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add lemon juice and cook for another 5 minutes,

Heat one tablespoon of oil in a pan, add the chicken breasts, fat-free mayonnaise, paprika, dried cranberries, celery, green onions, green bell pepper, pecans, seasoning salt, ground black pepper. Toss the chicken and mushrooms in a large bowl with the shredded chicken. Combine all the lime and soy dressing ingredients in a small jug or bowl, mix well and pour two-thirds of the dressing over the warm mushrooms. Arrange the salad leaves in a serving dish and toss through the remaining dressing. Top with the chicken and mushrooms and serve warm.

Rinse and drain lentils. Finely chop ginger, onion and garlic clove. Heat oil in a pot and saut chopped ginger, onion and garlic until softened. Add turmeric, hot chicken stock, crushed tomatoes and the lentils. Bring to boil and allow to simmer for 20 minutes. Puree the soup in a blender until smooth and return to the pot. Add coconut milk and heat gently.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish with nonstick pan coating or grease lightly with solid shortening. Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes. Place half in a prepared baking dish. Sprinkle half of the salt, pepper and bacon. Top with half of the sour cream & cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with chopped green onions to garnish.

In a small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Stir in sugar, vanilla, salt, and milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake. The amount of time will vary with the amount of sauce being reheated.

Heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onions and garlic and cook until softened and starting to brown, about 10 minutes. In food processor combine sour cream, cream cheese, onion mixture, parsley, salt and pepper. Refrigerate for at least one hour. Serve with chips, pita or vegetables.

Preheat oven to 350f. Mix butter, icing sugar, plain flour, cornflour, egg, sweetened condensed milk, golden syrup with 1 tbls of icing sugar mixture. Bake at 350f and 180c for 15 minutes. Cool on a wire rack and keep in an airtight container once cold.

Preheat oven to 325f. In a large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until well combined. Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla. In another bowl, with a whisk, mix flour, salt, and chocolate bars. Add dry ingredients to the butter mixture and mix together. Spread the mixture in an 8-inch square buttered pan. Bake for about 45 minutes. Put the pan on a wire rack and spread the caramel sauce on the cake while it is still hot. Let the cake cool in the pan.

Heat oil in a skillet over high heat. Brown chicken in two batches, 6 to 8 minutes. Set aside. In same skillet over medium heat, cook ginger, onion, and garlic, stirring until browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Add soy sauce, vinegar, and sugar. Cook over high heat until thick, 3 to 4 minutes. Add chicken. Stir to warm. Remove from heat. Stir in scallions.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. Place pie crust in a 9-inch tart pan and leave the sides long and free-form. Combine sugar and corn syrup. Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add pecans and vanilla, and teaspoon of melted butter and mix well. Set aside. Toss apples with lemon juice. Spread apples on bottom of pie crust and pour pecan mixture over apples. Fold edges of pie crust over filling. Bake pie until set, about 45 to 50 minutes.

In a saucepan combine ground beef, salt, worcestershire sauce, onion gravy mix, biscuit mix, milk, brown gravy mix, hot water. Bring to a boil over medium heat and continue. Stirring until thick. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.

Combine all ingredients in a food processor and blend until very smooth, 1-2 minutes. Refrigerate. Sauce may become quite thick once refrigerated. Just heat for a few seconds in microwave. Recipe can be doubled or tripled and the level of dees sweet and sour sauce can be adjusted to suit personal preferences.

Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. In medium bowl, whisk buttermilk, oil, and egg until blended. Stir into cornmeal mixture just until moistened. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cut cornbread into 9 squares.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees fahrenheit. Spread bottom crust in a 9 inch pie pan. Spread berry mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Dot butter on top. Put top crust on and seal edges. Poke several vent holes in top crust. Bake at 425 degrees fahrenheit for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 350 degrees fahrenheit, leaving pie in oven, and bake for 30 minutes longer.

Preheat oven to 400f. Place wax paper on a large baking sheet. Combine dry ingredients in a second bowl. Combine other ingredients in a second bowl. Blend the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients. Add butter and sugar. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 170 degrees celsius.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt. Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until throughly blended. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart onto prepared sheets. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, or until set. Remove cookies to wire rack to cool completely.

Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook turkey, onion, chilies and garlic in oil, stirring occasionally, until turkey is no longer pink in center and onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Place the rice in a large bowl and add cold water to cover by 3 inches. Swirl around with your fingers until the water becomes cloudy, then pour through a strainer to drain. Repeat this process until the water remains clear. This will take 4 to 6 rinsings. Place the rice, salt and the 6 cups water in a deep, nonstick saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer the rice gently, uncovered, for about 18 minutes. When the rice has absorbed all the water, reduce the heat to the lowest possible setting and sprinkle the butter pieces over the top. Wrap a clean kitchen towel around the pot lid, piling any excess cloth on top of the lid. Place the cloth-covered lid over the rice and steam for 20 minutes. Remove the pot from the heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Gently fluff the rice with a fork and serve immediately.

Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing and mix well. Squeeze the spinach to remove water. Add to the mixture and mix well. Add optional ingredient. Hollow out the bread and fill with the sour cream mixture. Arrange assorted cut up veggies and bread cubes around loaves.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Thaw potatoes between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture. Press into bottom and up sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Drizzle with butter. Bake for 25 minutes until lightly browned. Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper, stirring well. Pour over ham mixture. Bake at 425 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

Mix all ingredients except the rice and coconut milk in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat to a simmer and stir in the vanilla. Cook until just about all of the milk is absorbed, stirring occasionally. Stir in cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve warm or chilled.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Mix all the dry ingredients together. Mix everything together. Shape into 8-12 balls, put on cooked sheet lined with parchement. Flatten slightly. Leave room between them because the will spread out. Bake for 10-12 minutes at 350f.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. In a food processor, combine the cheese and butter. Process until the mixture is smooth. Add the scallions and pulse until combined. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Spread the cheese mixture on the cut sides of the bread. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden. Remove from oven and serve immediately.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the pork chops and cook until tender, about 5 minutes. Add the flour, worcestershire sauce, salt, and oregano and cook for another 5-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the pork chops and cook for another 5-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the flour, worcestershire sauce, salt, and ore

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, butter, sugar, egg, vanilla extract, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, flour. Add to the creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place rolls on ungreased baking sheet try to flatten rolls so they resemble flat circles. Take a spoonful of sauce and spread ontop of each rolls. Then cut up cheese into small bits and garnish. Add meat ontop of cheese and then place remaining cheese ontop of meat. Cook for about 15 min of until rolls are golden.

Heat olive oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisp- tender. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until broccoli is hot. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

Combine all ingredients together in blender. Pour into 6- 3oz molds or paper cups. Freeze for one hour, place sticks in the middle. Freeze for another 3 hours, until solid. To release nectarine, dip molds into hot water until pops loosen and slide out. If using paper cups, peel away paper.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan with nonstick spray. In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly with a fork. Add water and oatmeal and let stand until liquid is absorbed stir in remaining ingredients, except meat. Mix well. Add meat, using your hands or a sturdy spoon and mix until well blended. Shape into a loaf in your baking pan. Make an indentation down center of loaf and fill with ketchup. Bake for 1 hour or until loaf is done. Remove from oven and cover with foil--let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving and it will cut nicely.
Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add butter, onion, and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 to 4 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Cover with lid and cook for 10-15 minutes. Cover with lid and cook for 10-15 minutes. Cover and cook for 10-15 minutes. Cover and cook for 10-15

In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix into a soft dough. Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead 20 times. Divide dough into fourths and roll each quarter into a 12 inch long rope. Cut each rope into inch pieces, and set on a floured surface. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Roll each piece of dough across the tines of a fork to get groves on it and drop it into the pot of water. Cook gnocchi until it floats to the top. Drain and serve.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and two sugars until well combined. Beat in vanilla pudding mix. Add eggs, one at a time, until well incorporated. Mix in vanilla extract. In another small bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, and salt. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just incorporated. Fold in m&ms and white chocolate chips. Drop tablespoon size cookie dough onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes, or until just turning golden brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes before removing to wire rack to cool completely.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine the flours with the salt in a medium bowl. Add the milk, butter and eggs and whisk to combine thoroughly. Pour into well-greased muffin cups or a popover pan. Bake at 450 for 20 minutes, turn oven to 350 degrees and bake 15 minutes longer.

Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over med. Heat. Add steak and garlic. Cook until desired doneness. Stir in beans, chilis, and cilantro. Cook and stir 7 minutes. Spoon mixture on tortillas. Top with cheese. Garnish with salsa, sour cream.

Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook turkey, onion, chilies and garlic in oil, stirring occasionally, until turkey is no longer pink in center and onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a small bowl, toss the nuts with the maple syrup, olive oil, herbs and cayenne. Spread the nuts on a rimmed baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes., stirring occasionally, until browned. Season the nuts with salt and pepper and toss frequently until cooled.

Preheat oven to 400f. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Stir together dressing, butter, garlic salt, pepper, potato chips in a medium bowl. Add chicken and toss well to coat with mixture. Roll each piece in crushed chips and place on a shallow baking sheet. Sprinkle with any remaining chips. Bake for 30 minutes or until crispy and lightly browned.

Heat oven to 425. Cut the bottoms off the brussels sprouts and trim any damaged leaves. Cut in half. Add the rest of the ingredients into a bowl. Mix to combine. Add brussels sprouts and mix until coated. Put in a roasting pan in the oven for 45 minutes, stiring once after about 25 minutes, until brown and caramelized.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add eggs and sauté for 5 minutes. Add mayonnaise and sauté for another 5 minutes. Add more salt and pepper and cook for another 5 minutes. Add more salt and pepper and cook

Preheat oven to 400f. Peel, core and slice apples into a bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon, water and salt. Mix well to coat apples. Place in two ramikins or small au gratin dishes, sprayed with cooking spray. Dot with butter and spread cheese over top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until apples fall.

In a small saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch then whisk in soda until smooth. Bring to a boil and cook while stirring for 1 minute or until thickened. Cover and refrigerate until cool. In a large bowl, combine the spinach, sesame oil, sugar, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, dijon mustard, toasted sesame seeds. Add salt to your taste. Add cucumber mix to bowl, tossing to coat. Set aside at room temperature to marinate 30 minutes. Arrange chilled prepared spinach salad mix on plates. Spoon cucumber mixture on top.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. In a bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and butter with your hands. Press the mixture firmly into a 9-inch pie pan, and bake until brown, about 20 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow to cool to room temperature before filling. Lower the oven temperature to 325 degrees f. In a separate bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and butter with your hands. Whisk until well blended and place the filling in the cooled pie shell. Bake in the oven for 15 minutes and allow to chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Once chilled, combine the sour cream and powdered sugar and spread over the top of the pie using a spatula. Sprinkle the lime zest as a garnish on top of the sour cream and serve chilled.

Preheat oven to 350f. In small saucepan, melt butter and choc in saucepan over low heat. When melted ans smooth, set aside to cool. Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl till thick and creamy. Stir n cooled chocolate and golden syrup. Then add flour, cocoa, salt and nuts. Pour into tin, bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven, cool in tin then cut into squares.
In a 4-cup measuring cup, heat 4 cups water in microwave to boiling. Place tea bags in water and let steep for 5-10 minutes. Pour tea into pitcher and mix thoroughly. Set in refrigerator to chill.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. In a large bowl, cream brown sugar and melted butter. Add vanilla and eggs 1 at a time. In a separate bowl, sift flour, powder, and salt. Add dry mixture into wet mixture. Spread into a greased glass baking dish. Cook in oven until golden, 15-18 minutes. In a microwave safe bowl, heat peanut butter and cream on low heat. Stir until smooth, and spread over baked bars. Cool slightly and cut into bars.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 425. Place chicken breasts in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2. Spread 1 tsp butter on each of the four chicken breasts. Sprinkle salt and paprika on the breasts. Drizzle all with the lemon juice. Bake uncovered 35- 45 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with snipped parsley and serve.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until just moistened. Spoon into lined or nonstick, sprayed muffin pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove muffins from the tray and cool on a wire rack.

Preheat oven to 450f. Place potatoes in a large baking dish. Add remaining ingredients to the dish and toss until well coated. Bake uncovered about 50 minutes until tender and brown on the edges. Turn the potatoes halfway into cooking time and add more water if the water is all absorbed. Turn on the broiler for a few minutes to make them nice and brown.

Preheat oven to 375f. Grease 2 baking sheets. Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg. Set aside. Beat the butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer at high speed of an electric mixer until well blended. Beat in the eggs and apple juice. Gradually add the flour to the butter mixture, beating at low speed until well blended. Stir in the apple and pecans. Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto the prepared cookie sheets. Bake for 13 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on wire rack.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add in spinach and chopped garlic. Saute stirring for about 10-12 minutes or until all the liquid from the spinach evaporates. Add in the breadcrumbs and parmesan cheese. Mix to combine and heat through. Season with salt and fresh ground pepper to taste.

Heat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. In large skillet, brown beef and onion then drain. Return meat to pan. Add spaghetti sauce. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat into an ungreased 12 x 8 inch dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Unroll crescent roll dough over the top of the mixture. Mix parmesan cheese and butter together, then spread over the top of the dough. Bake 18-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix powdered drink mix with water. Pour into ice trays. Freeze. Prepare lemonade mix. Fill punch bowl or large pitcher. Add lemon-lime cubes and lime slices.

Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, eggs, yellow onion, bok choy, soy sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper, bamboo shoot, medium shrimp and saute for 5-6 minutes, stirring occasionally or until shrimp is pink. Remove from heat and stir in bok choy, soy sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper, bamboo shoot, medium shrimp and saute for 5-6 minutes, stirring occasionally or until shrimp is pink.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. Place chicken on a greased backing sheet and brush on egg whites. Cook for about 25 minute or unit chicken is done. Add mozzarella and return to oven for about 2 minutes for the cheese to melt. Add mozzarella

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

In a large mixing bowl, dissolve sugar and jell-o in 2 cups boiling water. Add to the jell-o mixture the juice of both oranges, the zest of one orange, chopped nuts, and the entire can of crushed pineapple. Shred apples and cranberries. Add to jell-o. Mix well. Chill overnight or until set.

Preheat oven to 350f. Cook ground beef, stirring occasionally until brown. Drain off fat. Stir in rice, soup, chilies, and taco seasoning mix. Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking pan. Top with tomatoes cheese and corn chips. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until heated through.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut chicken in half. Arrange, skin side up, in a roasting pan. Combine butter, lemon juice, and spices in a small bowl and mix well. Brush chicken with mixture. Roast until juices run clear. Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes.

In a large skillet, saute the meat with garlic and ginger root in oil for a couple minutes. Add the curry paste, coconut milk, lime rind and juice. Simmer until meat is desired tenderness, or until tofu is heated through. Stir in the cilantro just before serving. Serve with rice.

Place chicken in slow cooker. Combine salad dressing mix and water. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 3 hours. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and soup until blended. Stir in mushrooms, pour over chicken, and cook 1 hour longer or until chicken juices run clear. Serve over rice or noodles.
Drain and reserve liquid from fruit. Add enough water to make two cups of liquid. Pour pudding mix & liquid into a pan. Cook until thickened, stir in dry jello. Mix in pineapple and oranges. Chill.

Preheat oven to 350f. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until throughly blended. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart onto prepared sheets. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, or until set. Remove cookies to wire rack to cool completely.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt, and set aside. In a measuring cup or small bowl, whisk together all of the wet ingredients, except the cider vinegar. Add the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients, and whisk well to combine. Pour batter into greased 9inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

Preheat oven to 400, grease 2 quart casserole dish. In prepared casserole dish, place chicken, broccoli and cheese. In a separate mixing bowl, blend baking mix, milk, eggs, salt and pepper on high speed until well mixed. Pour into dish over chicken, broccoli and cheese. Bake for 35-40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 350. In a large bowl combine the butter, cheese and mustard. Spread on cut surfaces of bread. Place on foil covered baking sheet. Bake at 425 for 7 to 10 minutes or until spread has melted and is a light golden brown. To serve, slice diagonally.

Preheat oven to 350f. Cut up the apples into small chunks and place them on the bottom of a lightly greased pie pan. Combine the sugar, flour, eggs and half of the vanilla into a bowl and mix well. Pour the mixture over the apples and sprinkle with remaining vanilla. Put into preheated oven for 20-30 minutes.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well. Cover and refrigerate until cool. Preheat oven to 400, grease 2 quart casserole dish. In prepared casserole dish, place chicken, broccoli and cheese. In a separate mixing bowl, blend baking mix, milk, eggs, salt and pepper on high speed until well mixed. Pour into dish over chicken, broccoli and cheese. Bake for 35-40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 375. Place tart apples in a 2-quart square baking dish. Stir in the tart apples. For topping, in a medium bowl combine the oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, butter, whipped cream. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in the nuts. Sprinkle topping over filling. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until fruit is tender and topping is golden. Cool slightly. Serve warm with ice cream if desired.
